 :constitutional-discipline
 {:civic-wayfinding-not-target-list
  "G10 — a map to help a citizen FIND a service; NEVER an attack-surface / SPOF / weak-point map of the state (Transparent Force discipline, §1.12).",
  :freshness-gated
  "G12 — stale entries flagged :stale; downstream consumers (esp. toritsugi G14) MUST re-verify before any citizen-facing action.",
  :murakumo-only-inference
  "G7 — Murakumo-only inference (ADR-2605215000).",
  :neutrality
  "G11 — jurisdiction-neutral + politically neutral; descriptive only; no ranking of governments.",
  :no-personal-data
  "G6 — government org data + public role-contact (switchboard / 窓口) only; NEVER an individual official's private/home contact; data-minimized.",
  :non-commercial
  "G8 — non-profit public good; no resale of the atlas as a data product (Charter Rider §2(e)).",
  :non-fabrication
  "G5 — every unit/address/window/form/procedure carries provenance + last-verified + sourcing (:authoritative | :representative); :representative rows are illustrative and NEVER counted as coverage; procedures must cite legal-basis.",
  :agent-not-official-channel
  "G3 — the per-unit atlas DID (did:web:etzhayyim.com:gov:<iso3>:...) is an etzhayyim support-agent record for a real public body; it NEVER claims to BE the government, NEVER is an official channel, NEVER issues/accepts anything on a government's behalf (§2(c) impersonation ban). The DID-doc declares the agent/mirror relation + links the body's official-url / official-did.",
  :public-data-only
  "G4 — only public official sources; respect robots.txt / ToS / rate-limits; no behind-auth access; no circumvention.",
  :member-authorized-support
  "G9 — ooyake may guide, draft, prepare, track, and hand off administrative activity for an etzhayyim member, but every external submission/payment/signature or government-record mutation requires explicit member consent, applicable legal/licensed boundaries, and an audit trail. It is an agent/support service, not the government and not an official channel."},
